Interface BoundsExpr

public interface BoundsExpr

Defines implementing Objects as having a Bounds definition.

Details

  1. The Location of a BoundsExpr is defined by the X and Y coordinate values.
  2. The Dimensions of a BoundsExpr is defined by the Width and Height coordinate values.
  3. The Type of the Location Coordinates for this BoundsExpr is defined by the abstract locType() method.
  4. See Bounds for the immutable, default implementation of BoundsExpr.
